Web language, runs in browsers and servers, flexible, has weird type behavior

Common value sizes:

| Type | Size |
| --- | --- |
| Number | 8 bytes for the IEEE 754 double value |
| BigInt | variable size |
| Boolean | engine-dependent |
| String | usually 2 bytes per UTF-16 code unit, plus object overhead |
| Symbol | engine-dependent |
| Object / Array / Function | engine-dependent, includes object overhead |
| null / undefined | engine-dependent |

Typed array element sizes are fixed:

| Typed array element | Size |
| --- | --- |
| Int8 / Uint8 / Uint8Clamped | 1 byte |
| Int16 / Uint16 | 2 bytes |
| Int32 / Uint32 / Float32 | 4 bytes |
| Float64 / BigInt64 / BigUint64 | 8 bytes |
